<br>
Nukes: Honestly, they're really not half bad...obviously they're not the best, as they aren't meant to...but i've been in NToV and I was able to nuke most of the dragons in there either with magic or fire.  The only problem is I don't see myself doing any real damage, even though I know I am.  It's not as drastic as a wizard or a druid nuke.<br>
<br>
DS: Used to be good...Now it's just an extra FR buff and one point advantage.  The 38 DS Utadin was referring to was self only.  Sure, I DS during raids, but that's a one mage job.  Why do I have 3-5 mages per raid here?  /frown<br>
<br>
Summons (CoH?): This used to be so damn uber...we could clear agro from anyone anywhere anytime, including ourselves.  Now it's nerfed so that the caster has to be a fairly good distance away, or aggro will remain.  This also means that I can't clear my own agro anymore.  I saved countless raids with CoH, and enhanced them with CoH back in the day.  Now it's a late person retriever and an &quot;Oops, I fucked pulling and need another chance&quot; spell.<br>
<br>
Escape Spells: Gate?  Yeah, that's about it.  Whatever...<br>
<br>
Epic:  It's funny how Utadin says not that hard...when he holds the pos in his hand... /flip.  And if you really think about it, this whole game is based on luck.  Loots and how hard you get hit for.  Sure you can upgrade yourself, but when it comes down to it, it's just a roll of weighted dice.  Throw this million sided die.  If it lands on 5, or 783,203 - you receive an earth staff.<br>
<br>
General: Before Kunark, we were golden.  It was so powa to be a mage, our pets soloed everything and everyone.  We were on top.  Then Kunark came and smashed us to pieces compared to other classes who gained leaps and bounds...except for a nice new spell called CoH.  What a useful tool!  Oh wait, sorry...that's over now.  Too bad.  I think all classes got mana regen except clerics and us, correct me if I'm wrong.  Now I don't really think it's that bad for clerics, because they're not known for soloing, right?  Mages on the other hand solo quite a bit...we get an hp regen...why not mana?  /boggle  (Oh yeah, thanks for the cleric overwrites not stacking with my armor...how about making it take a 3pp item instead of 47 2cp items?)  Overall in velious, I found myself pretty useless until we got into north ToV recently.  Pets always got smoked by AE, or when the bug was in, aggro'd way early and smoked.  I don't think I've summoned a pet for a while, which makes me wonder why I'm bothering with the epic...Anyways, lots of nukes are resisted because verant was too lazy to program resistances how they should have.  But that goes along with everything else Verant has done.  So anyways, sure I make mod rods...sure I CoH extra people in to raids to help out or to save my puller...sure I summon the water or food or arrows or whatever to make those little minor things happen...Oh yeah, I can mala too so it's overwritten by malo (/rude verant).  Let me ask you this...why have more than one mage per raid?  Is it necessary?  I can't really see that it is.  Get more wizards...get more druids...get more anything...you only need one mage...  Every other class you should have at least two of...and the only one I can think of that only requires two is enchanters.  And no, I'm not forgetting the &quot;useless&quot; shadow knights, but I've seen them make some of the best pulls ever...so I believe you need those.<br>
<br>
Wow, that was long.<br>
